      "created": "2016-11-15T18:52:25.383+0000",
      "description": "When a guaranteed container arrives at an NM but there are no resources to start its execution, opportunistic containers will be killed to make space for the guaranteed container.\n\nAt the moment, we kill opportunistic containers in reverse order of arrival (first the most recently started ones). This is not always the right decision. \nFor example, we might want to minimize the number of containers killed: to start a 6GB container, we could kill one 6GB opportunistic or three 2GB ones. \nAnother example would be to refrain from killing containers of jobs that are very close to completion (we have to pass job completion information to the NM in that case).",
      "priority": {
        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/priority/3",
        "iconUrl": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/priorities/major.svg",
        "name": "Major",
        "id": "3"
      },
      "resolution": null,
